    A multi threaded version of Text2TextConverter where the composer is started in a separate worker thread. See AbstractConverter for details about error handling and manipulating data.

    As a rule of thumb while working with normal files on disc, don't use this concurrent version unless your input normally exceeds at least 1MB of data, as the overhead of starting a new thread and synchronizing threads are otherwise greater than the gain by the concurrency.
